JO  - Management Science
SP  - 724
EP  - 733
VL  - 34
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We show, for a wide variety of payoff functions, that the expected log optimal portfolio is also game theoretically optimal in a single play or in multiple plays of the stock market. Thus there is no essential conflict between good short-term and long-run performance. Both are achieved by maximizing the conditional expected log return.
AB  - We show, for a wide variety of payoff functions, that the expected log optimal portfolio is also game theoretically optimal in a single play or in multiple plays of the stock market. Thus there is no essential conflict between good short-term and long-run performance. Both are achieved by maximizing the conditional expected log return.
